The paper discusses improving policies in cooperative partially observable games, which is a topic that falls under the umbrella of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of search techniques to improve policies is a common approach in game theory (cs.GT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also deals with multi-agent systems (cs.MA) and the ability to interpret the actions of others, which is a topic in systems and control (cs.SY).
